abstract: As a curative agent the snake, dead or alive, is thought highly of. abstract: Storehouse K of Woodruff's s Stores, in Brooklyn, was a smoldering ruin yesterday. The front and rear walls were standing intact, but the greater portion of the south wall had fallen, showing within masses of charred timber, jute, and sisal grass partially consumed. abstract: CHICAGO, July 1 -- Every rail on the Rock Island Road at Blue Island, sixteen miles from this city, is blocked to traffic, rendering futile any attempt to get trains into or out of Chicago. A notice, reading, "All trains abandoned until further notice," confronted the public at the Van Buren Street station, and told in a few words the completely paralyzed condition of Rock Island traffic at this end of the line.

abstract: WINNIPEG, Manitoba, July 1 -- The strike on the Northern Pacific Railway arising out of the Pullman difficulty has finally spread to that portion of the system in Manitoba. The railroad officials were greatly surprised, having been confident that the trouble would not extend to the Canadian portion of the line.

abstract: There is something unique about Brighton Beach race track. abstract: KINGSTON, N.Y., July 8. -- No rain of any account has fallen in Ulster County for a month, and the country is experiencing a disastrous drought. Berries and small fruit are drying on the bushes, and the crops this year will be failures. Roads are deep with dust, and meadow land is burned gray. In Dutchess County the land is even dryer, and all crops are suffering greatly for rain.

abstract: UNION STOCK YARDS, CHICAGO, July 8. -- Shortly before 3 o'clock this afternoon the Chicago and Eastern Illinois Railroad attempted to run a train of twenty cars, laoded with coal, into the city. abstract: SAN FRANCISCO, July 10 -- The crisis at Sacramento will be reached soon. United States troops left for that city early this morning. They were armed and equipped as for a campaign. abstract: CLEVELAND, July 24 -- There was such a heavy track for the Grand Circuit meeting to-day that instead of starting at noon, as originally intended, nothing was done till after 3 o'clock. The 2:35 trot for three-year-olds, which looked sure for Red Bud, with two heats in hand, terminated in a very unexpected fashion.

abstract: From The Cincinnati Enquirer. Five monkeys escaped from their cage at Kohl  Middleton's Museum on Monday. abstract: There is a story of a French dog whose breakfast was forgotten, whereupon he ran out into the garden, and returning with a sprig in his mouth, deposited it at his master's feet. abstract: HARTFORD, July 30. -- The forty-two members of the historical pilgrimage party which left Philadelphia early this morning reached here at 2:05 this afternoon. They were met at the station by Charles Dudley Warner, James J. Goodwin, P.H. Woodward, Secretary of the Board of Trade; the Rev. J.H. Twitchell, Forrest Morgan, Secretary F.B. Gay, and other members of the Connecticut Historical Society, and were driven to the United States Hotel, where luncheon was served.
